Counts One and Three and Five: Conspiracy to Violate Federal Laws- The Statute

The relevant statute for Counts One, Three and Five is Title 18, United States Code, Section 371, which provides that "if two or more people conspire [] to commit any offense against the United States . . . and one or more of such persons do any act to effect the object of the conspiracy," each person is guilty of a federal crime.
